						               													<description>Jurors, will you make the right decision?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Slip into the shoes of a juror, judge a criminal case and deliver your verdict.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Quebec band JAZZEUR BOR&amp;Eacute;AL is on tour in Europe. Is their backing singer responsible for causing a fire and the death of a show technician?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Intime Conviction, players embody a group of jurors for an evening or a week. First, they will have to analyze the facts against the accused. Once all the actions of the juror cards have been completed, the game ends with a final vote where the players will have to decide by majority whether or not the accused is guilty in a criminal case.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In pairs or more, the participants will see their opinions put to the test more than once over the cards and the debates! During the final vote, it is alone in the face of their intimate conviction that they will have to find the way to victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play with friends for an evening by recreating the atmosphere of a closed session! Or make the fun last by revealing only a few items a day!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Content:&amp;#10;- 1 Rule of the game&amp;#10;- 1 Portrait of the accused &amp;amp; her statement&amp;#10;- 1 Scene of the crime&amp;#10;- 12 Juror Cards&amp;#10;- 1 Discovery Pass&amp;#10;- 24 Final Voting Cards&amp;#10;- 3 sealed fact sheets&amp;#10;- 1 FINAL REVELATION! To reveal at the end of the game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Intime conviction is a craft object entirely designed, made and assembled by hand and in Belgium. The format of the game is unusual as well: this game is in an envelope.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
